.TH _printf 3 "April 2026" "1.0" "holbertonschool-printf"

.SH NAME
_printf - prints output based on a specific format

.SH SYNOPSIS
#include "main.h"

int _printf(const char *format, ...);

.SH DESCRIPTION
The _printf function prints output depending on the format string.

The format string can contain normal text and special formats that start
with the % character. After %, there is a specifier like %s, %c, %%, %d, or %i.

The supported specifiers are:

.TP
.B %c
Prints a single character.

.TP
.B %s
Prints a string.

.TP
.B %%
Prints the % character.

.TP
.B %d
Prints an integer number.

.TP
.B %i
Prints an integer (same as %d).

.SH RETURN VALUE
The function returns the total number of characters printed,
not including the null byte.

If format is NULL, the function returns -1.

